									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/larissapham/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-3.07.30-PM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-10-at-3.07.30-PM-300x300.png 2x" alt="Larissa Pham" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/larissapham/">Larissa Pham</a></h6>
										Larissa Pham is the author of <em>Pop Song</em>, an essay collection, and the forthcoming novel <em>Discipline</em>. She hates colonialism but loves bánh mì.																			</div>
